page.title: 09A day in my life.
page.content:
A typical day for me starts at 7.00am when I am woken by my alarm. I quickly wash,dress and brush my hair then find my books ready for the lessons that day. I go out the house at 9.00 and arrive at school for 9.10 when the bell goes. I get home from school at 3.30pm and watch television. At 4.00 I do any homework which finishes at 6.00. I then get ready to go out with my friends. We usually go to the telephone box and ring{Talkabout.}This is where people between the ages of 13 and 17 phone other people. You can talk to a person and arrange to meet them if you wish. At about 9.50 we start for home. When I get in I usually watch television again if there is anything good to watch. If there isn't I go to bed.
By Maria Brock.
